Package Chat

Class Summary
AddMessageCommand Description of AddMessageCommand: This is where one can send messages using the ChatCommand to send messages through the ChatServer.
ChatClientStart Description of ChatClientStart: This is where the ChatClientStart is launched using the information of the client name, host, and port number.
ChatCommand<T> Description of ChatCommand: This is an abstract class called ChatCommand that implements Serializable and creates a final long with a serialVersionUID that creates the thread as a unique identifier.
ChatPanelDesigner Description of ChatPanelDesigner: This class extend JPanel and it designs the ChatPanel, it contains a serialVersionUID that creates the thread as a unique identifier and contains many components of a GUI.
DisconnectChatCommand Description of DisconnectChatCommand: This class is responsible for taking the actions of the user to disconnect the chat server when prompted to do so.
UpdateActiveTextCommand Description of UpdateActiveTextCommand: The UpdateActiveTextCommand updates the text that a user is entering from their given server to display on everyones computer at the same time.
UpdateChatCommand Description of UpdateChatCommand: This class updates the text that the user is entering as a message to all the users on the document editor.
UserTextStatusCommand Description of UserTextStatusCommand: This class shows when the user may be typing right above the message bar.
